✨ THE PRESETS ARE FINALLY HERE!!! ✨🎉

STORYTIME…

I remember the days frustrated and spending HOURS at my computer trying to find and nail my “style”.

Even though I had a clear vision and idea of what I wanted my photos to feel like, I just couldn’t figure out how to achieve it… So many confusing buttons and tweaks and color grades to study… it was all so overwhelming.

It took me YEARS to feel like I had finally created a preset I was confident in AND felt reflected both my personality and the persoanlity of my clients.

When I did, it changed EVERYTHING. Suddenly I was attracting like minded clients who valued “warm but not to warm, happy, genuine, timeless” photos - and an experience that matched!

When I looked at my photos the colors made me feel excited — and I want for these presets to do the same for you and your clients! 🥰

So my hope launching  these presets is that you, too, can finally feel CONFIDENT and INSPIRED by the work that you do – not only when you’re taking the photos, but that the inspiration would continue as you open up your laptop on a Monday morning and edit with coffee in hand and a smile on your face. ☕️😊 

SO, ALL THAT SAID IT’S TIME FOR ME TO SHARE THE SECRET SAUCE WITH YOU – THE WS PRESETS ARE HERE! Click the link in my bio to get your hands on them today and change your editing game for good! 🎉

Helloooo summer — it is time for me to emerge from my Instagram posting hiatus and share the work I do nearly undercover these days! 😂🤍

Leah + Charlie taking golden hour summer nights to a whole other level of SWOON 😍

Truthfully? I get INCREDIBLY overwhelmed by sharing wedding content these days. 😮‍💨

I’ve shot so many incredible days already this year and have shared precisely zero. Not because every one of them wasn’t inspiring and magical — they were. I’ve been shooting more pictures per wedding day than I ever have before. Beautiful moments. But honestly, instagram (for me) has been the least inspiring place for me to put them. 

Posting only for them to be valued and pushed up the feed by likes and affirmative comments that it’s what people like to see or what’s trending — which is so far from why I take these photos or do this work. 

The greatest place I can put these photos after they’ve been taken is back in the hands of my clients. Back to their homes. 🤍

I’m not saying marketing isn’t important, I’m not even saying my lack of posting is the wise move business wise (😂) but 8 years into this refining journey of being a wedding photographer and never have I felt less of a call to submit my work to the approval of man — or in this case, the endless algorithm that asks for more of me and the “next thing” every week.

So there’s my honest update. It’s been a really secret place lately — exchanging photos only between the camera, computer, my client, and I. No crowd clapping in the comments every weekend or saving posts and drawing inspiration from my poses/locations. My follower count is not growing and many will surpass me in the benchmark to whatever number of followers is considered “alot”… it seems that number continues to climb. What used to be 10k is now thousands more. What is more will one day still not be enough. Anyone tired? 😅

I wonder if I’m alone, but if I’m not, I’d love to hear from you and encourage my fellow photo friends as we work tirelessly through this busy season that the greatest place we can place our work is back in the hands of God and the special people we take these photos for, the rest will come — or it won’t, and that’s equally okay. I’ve been quiet, but my soul has never felt better or more proud of the work being done. 😌🤍

Let’s do this, @chasebsander!! 🤍

📷: @auroragrace_

Baby #2 is a GIRL!!!!!! 🩷🩷🩷

We are so in love, so excited, and so thankful for this little girly to join our family!

And to our Jacker boy, you were made for this role and we can’t wait to watch you be a big brother. 🥹🥹

Well hi! It’s me, Whitley on your feed (alongside my family 🤍)

Popping on with some updated photos after realizing I managed to post close to nothing on my feed for the entire busy season of 2023 😂

It’s a FULL life these days. Balancing a near full time workload in a part time schedule to have the opportunity to spend some of my week fully home with Jack. While I may have had to skip out on the consistent social media posting this year, I am so proud of all the unseen that was accomplished. 

20 beautiful Minnesota weddings photographed, 140+ portrait sessions, countless hours editing, 30 weeks growing our baby girl, and many many days at home chasing our wild, crazy, hilarious toddler.

I can’t thank all of my amazing clients enough for entrusting me with their own lives and stories for me to capture and in turn, for the joy and privilege of getting to do what I love both in and outside of our home. 🤍

I’d be willing to bet this is the last thing to hit the feed before I announce a baby (anyone wanna guess her name?!) .. but hopefully I can recap a few of those shoots and weddings before then. 😜

So until whatever is next, I just wanted to extend a WARM thank you to all who have supported my business year after year and as the seasons change. 🤍 I am truly forever grateful to live out what 18 year old me once dreamt of — it’s better, more beautiful (and harder haha) than I ever could have imagined! 

Photos by my genius friend @auroragracephoto
